This is a mirror of http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=3975

after set g:paths in finder.vim , you can find your file by press <C-f> then input regular expression(now only support python's regular) to find file, it will open an window which list all the files that founded.

move cursor to the file path that you want to open,
press <Enter>, it will hide the find result window and edit the file in last window.
press <Space>,same as <Enter> but keep the find result window
press <ESC>  to close the findResult window.

Need python support.

Get lasted version on github: https://github.com/xieyu/Finder


